OL,6,F"There can be no doubt that the
OL,7,Fattacker was this knife-wielding
OL,8,Fdefendant.
OL,10,F"Mr Thomas was struck by the knife on
OL,11,Ffive occasions in different places in
OL,12,Fwhat was, you may think, a frenzied
OL,13,Fattack.
OL,15,F"If you were walking home across the
OL,16,Fcommon minding your own business and
OL,17,Fsomeone ran at you with a large knife
OL,18,Fyou would have been terrified `
OL,19,Fclearly so was Mr Thomas.
