OL,6,F"Having stabbed Mr Thomas, the
OL,7,Fdefendant left him for dead and went
OL,8,Fon the run, only being arrested a
OL,9,Fmonth later at the carnival."
OL,11,FGiving evidence, Williams claimed he
OL,12,Facted in self-defence after the victim
OL,13,Fproduced a knife.
OL,15,FHe claimed he had been looking to talk
OL,16,Fto the bus driver about his
OL,17,Frelationship with his daughter. He
OL,18,Ftold jurors he took the knife from Mr
OL,19,FThomas and stabbed him with it.
